description.value: Terracotta pyramidal loom-weight.  A mould-made pyramidal loom-weight, with truncated top; a hole is pierced from side to side near the top, the piercing indicated by slightly raised rings, probably caused during the piercing process. On one side is an oval impression from an intaglio gem of two human figures standing close together, facing each other, probably a male homosexual incident.  Solid; two-piece mould, the join running along opposite corners. Micaceous orange-brown Nile silt with a pink core.
